Execute the samples in the $XCRYPT/multilang directory as follows:
(This limitation should be fixed soon.)

(1) Execute the Ruby sample scripts
% ruby sample/use_limit_rb.rb            # uses the limit module defined in Ruby
% ruby sample/use_limit_lsp.rb           # uses the limit module defined in Lisp

(2) Execute the Perl sample scripts
% xcrypt sample/use_limit_lsp.xcr        # uses the limit module defined in Lisp

(3) Execute the Lisp sample script
;; Now only Allegro Common Lisp with quicklisp is supported.
% alisp
CL-USER> (load "client.lisp")
CL-USER> (load "sample/range-xcr.lisp")  # uses the limit module defined in Perl

(4) Execute the Python sample scripts
% python sample/single-xcr.py            # Submit a single job.
% python sample/use_dry.py               # uses the dry module defined in Perl
% python sample/use_dry_py.py            # uses the dry module defined in Python
% python sample/use_limit_py.py          # uses the limit module defined in Python
